item.title: D14
item.dc:creator: Teo
item.excerpt:encoded: Experience circularity from a broad value network perspective based on a new culture of collaboration between many stakeholders. Explore aspects of reversible building design and data sharing to preserve the value of materials during construction, use and transformation phases. Learn about the Building Circular Assessment prototype and which policies can support market players to create new business opportunities whilst reducing waste generation and CO2 emissions.

Le projet doit repondre diffrents dfis et chelles, en fonction des contraintes cologiques mais egalement des opportunits urbanistiques. Au macro niveau urbain, laccent est mis sur la relation paysagre et la perception des abords de la Meuse, le btiment tant une reprsentation de la nature mosane (rochers, eau, vgtation). Il sagit de crer une synergie avec les zones attenantes, une zone intgre dans le paysage, zone buffer entre le magnifique paysage de la Meuse, les usagers du futur batiment et les activits agressives industrielles larrire. A lchelle de son utilisation, le btiment doit rpondre aux critres levs de performance nergtique, grer et intgrer positivement les contraintes du site.

PARKRESIDENTIE PROJECT OP DEN DIJK PARKRESIDENTIE

OOSTENDSESTEENWEG St. PIETERSMOLENSTRAAT
anne: 2014 fonction:logements phase: esquisse maitre douvrage:Studie En Expertisebureau De Palmenaer surface: 4140m2 The site has a prominent location in the blue green network at the territorial scale of Brugge. It represents a major open space in the North West quarter (delimitedby the canal Gent-Oostende and Boudewijnkannal) within the radial structure of the city. The site is situated next to Sint Pietersplas, a recreational spot,equipped for different sport activities such as nautical sports. Op den Dijk project foresees a very low energy housing development taking in account ecological issues at the level of neighbourhood.
